               <h1 class="font-s2 font-w1 color-2 font-fam1 text-c">Overview</h1>
               <!-- <h2 class="font-s3 font-w1 color-2 font-fam1 text-c developed">Developed A Music Streaming App For Music Lovers To Listen To Millions Of Track.</h2> -->
                <p class="font-s3 line-h font-fam1 font-w4 text-c color-2 possible open"> <strong>Pro Health</strong> has been operating as a local pharmacy in the USA since 1965. The company takes great pleasure in providing timely service and giving patients a one-stop shop for their medication requirements. Among the many services offered by <strong>Pro Health,</strong> some of the most common are terminal illness care services, medication synchronization, and drug flavoring. Not only this, they create technologies that support future direct-to-patient health care and offer comfort that puts patients first.</p>
                <p class="font-s3 line-h font-fam1 font-w4 text-c color-2 open">Unfortunately, <strong>Pro Health</strong> lagged in showing everything it had to offer, making sales, and driving visitors to its pharmacy websites. The company recognized the need for widely accessible, digitally accessible e-health products for all patients, irrespective of patient's age, level of digital literacy, or physical or mental impairments that prevent them from taking full advantage of an app's features. To reach a wider audience and eventually boost sales, they contacted a reputable pharma application development company, <strong>BitsWits</strong>, to work with them on developing a prescription delivery app.</p>
